[1 (p. 83)] [Kyrie I] Grave : [for SATB without text, vl1, vl2, ob1/tpt1, ob2, tpt2, b(org) : used by Handel for "No more to Ammon's god and king" in Jephtha, HWV 70 no. 3] -- [2. p. 84-85] [Christe] Vivace [SATB without text, vl1, v2l, org (b) : used by Handel for "Pour forth no more" in Jephtha, HWV 70 no. 2] -- [3, p. 86-87] [Kyrie II] Alla breve : Kyrie eleison [fragment of text on p. 87] : [for SATB vl1, vl2, tpt1, tpt2, org(b) : [not used by Handel] -- [4, p. 88-89] [Cum sancto spiritu] Allegro : [for SATB, vl1, vl2, tpt1, tpt2, org(b) : used by Handel for "Chermosh we no more will adore" in the chorus "No more Ammon's god and king" in Jephtha, HWV 70, no. 3] -- [5, p. 90] [Osanna in excelsis] Alla breve : Theme sublime of every praise : [SATB, vl1/2 : used by Handel for "Theme sublime of every praise" in Jephtha, HWV 70; no. 39]
